  <recipe id="Haferflockentr&#252;ffel">
    <head>
      <title>Haferflockentr&#252;ffel</title>
      <subtitle>Chocolate-oatmeal drops</subtitle>
      <categories>
        <cat class="main">Cookies</cat>
        <cat class="region">Germany</cat>
        <cat class="diet">Egg-free</cat>
				<cat class="diet">Nut-free</cat>
      </categories>
    </head>
    <description><xhtml:p>Renate proclaimed this the BEST recipe, because it is simple and delicious. The entire Buchmann family loves them, and Tobi usually starts eating before they've completely cooled.</xhtml:p>

<xhtml:p>The first time I made these I mis-translated "Haferflocken." It was not good, but we tried them anyhow.</xhtml:p></description>
    <ingredients system="US">
      <ing-div>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>2</qty>
            <unit>Tb</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>sweet butter</item>
<!--2 Tb sweet butter-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1 3/4</qty>
            <unit>c</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>sugar</item>
<!--1 3/4 c. sugar-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1</qty>
            <unit>tsp</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>vanilla</item>
<!--1 tsp. vanilla-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>3</qty>
            <unit>Tb</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>cocoa</item>
<!--3 Tb. cocoa-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>1/2</qty>
            <unit>c</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>milk</item>
<!--1/2 c. milk-->
        </ing>
        <ing>
          <amt>
            <qty>3</qty>
            <unit>c</unit>
          </amt>
          <item>rolled oats</item>
<!--3 c. rolled oats-->
        </ing>
      </ing-div>
    </ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>In a medium saucepan, combine butter, sugar, vanilla, cocoa and milk. Bring to a boil over medium or medium-high heat, and allow to cook for 30 to 60 seconds. Remove from heat, and stir in oats until completely coated with chocolate mixture.</step>
      <step>Working quickly, drop the oats by teaspoonsful onto a baking sheet lined with wax paper or parchment paper. Allow to cool and enjoy!</step>
    </directions>
  </recipe>
